Lizeka Tandwa, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - Cocaine worth an estimated street value of R78m was confiscated at the Oliver Tambo International Airport by SARS Customs officials on Saturday.&nbsp;Sars group executive Babs Naidoo said this marks the biggest ever cocaine bust by customs officials in South Africa.&nbsp;En route from Sao Paulo to Nairobi, Kenya, the 271kg of narcotics were found in a cargo warehouse during routine operations.&ldquo;The specific shipment indicated as cosmetics on official documentation, was identified for closer inspection through customs profiling techniques.&rdquo; &nbsp;Naidoo said a physical inspection was conducted after narcotic detector dogs reacted positively to the cargo. Officials found hair products packed in boxes.&nbsp;&ldquo;A drug test on a number of randomly selected containers all gave an immediate positive reaction to Cocaine.&rdquo; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.